title: The cabinet's last order of business.
on-arrival: unemployed -= 2; economic_growth += 1; inflation += 2; schleicher_approval += 1

After weeks of delay, Gereke finally presents his public works program to the cabinet. Though too late to save Schleicher’s tenure, it is approved by the chancellor and signed by Hindenburg without objection. The plan allocates half a billion marks to infrastructure projects across the Reich.

In the coming months, as millions of unemployed Germans return to work, it is not Schleicher, but his successor, who will reap the political rewards.